Sentencas: A cubic perovskite oxide SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-delta (SFC) is investigated as a novel cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of novel cobalt-free perovskite SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of SFC is close to that of typical Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CGO) electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of novel cobalt-free perovskite SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of SFC sample reached 25-54 S cm(-1) over the temperature range of 500-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of novel cobalt-free perovskite SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: According to analysis results of AC impedance spectroscopy and DC polarization measurement, the polarization resistance (R-p) of SFC as cathode material on CGO electrolyte was successfully reduced to 0.14 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of novel cobalt-free perovskite SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Two main oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) processes are identified in accordance with the oxygen partial pressure dependence of R-p, in which the rate limiting step for the ORR is the oxygen ion transfer within the bulk electrode and/or from electrode to CGO electrolyte through the triple phase boundary (TPB).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of novel cobalt-free perovskite SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The excellent electrochemical performance indicated that SFC can be a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of novel cobalt-free perovskite SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
